During the preparation of this manuscript , Lin et al. reported an independent mouse line in which the PGC-1 gene was targeted [ 37 ] .
Phenotypic comparison of the our PGC-1-deficient line with that of Lin et al. reveals a number of similarities and several interesting differences .
Both PGC-1-deficient lines exhibit cold intolerance , reduced hepatocyte <termsem="GO:0045333"> respiration </term> rates , and neurologic lesions .
However , a number of interesting differences are notable .
First , in contrast to Lin et al. , the PGC-1  /  mice described here do not exhibit any postnatal mortality .
Second , we did not find evidence for a defect in <termsem="GO:0006094"> gluconeogenesis </term> based on fasting blood glucose levels ( unpublished data ) .
